Little
Sally
Hamlin

Sally
Emery
Hamlin
is
the
daughter
of
Dr.
C.
Hamlin,
of

Brooklyn,
N.
Y.
Her
grandfather
was
Gen.
Chas.
Hamlin,
of

Maine,
graduate
of
Bowdoin
College,
Reporter
of
Decisions
of

the
Maine
Supreme
Court,
Speaker
of
the
Maine
House.
He

wrote
many
essays
on
law.
During
the
Civil
War
he
served
on

the
staff
of
Gen.
A.
A.
Humphreys
as
adjutant
general
and
took

part
in

of
Gettysburg
and
for

services
he

of

ficially

division

In
1865

army,

brevetted
Brigadier
